## Installation

This project uses [pixi](https://pixi.sh) for environment management.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_username }}/{{ project_name }}.git
cd {{ project_name }}
just setup
```

## Quick start

```python
from {{ package_name }} import analysis
```

## Project structure

```
├── data/                        # Raw, processed, and external data (not tracked)
├── notebooks/                   # Exploratory Jupyter notebooks
├── results/                     # Figures, tables, and reports
├── src/{{ package_name }}/      # Importable Python package
│   ├── analysis/
│   ├── data/
│   ├── visualization/
│   └── utils/
├── tests/                       # Test suite
├── config/                      # Configuration files
├── pixi.toml                    # Dependency manifest
├── pyproject.toml               # Build, lint, type-check, and test config
└── justfile                     # Task runner
```

## Development

```bash
just test        # Run the test suite
just lint        # Lint with ruff
just format      # Format with ruff
just typecheck   # Run mypy
just check       # All of the above
just notebook    # Start Jupyter Lab
just clean       # Remove caches and build artifacts
```

## Data

Raw data lives in `data/raw/` and is never modified directly.
See `data/README.md` for instructions on obtaining the data.

